<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Transparent Background Testing</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 2em;
            background: transparent;
        }
        .transparency-demo {
            background: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.3);
            border: 2px dashed #ff0000;
            padding: 2em;
            margin: 1em 0;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
        .overlay-demo {
            background: rgba(0, 0, 255, 0.5);
            color: white;
            padding: 1em;
            margin: 1em 0;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .checkerboard {
            background-image:
                linear-gradient(45deg, #ccc 25%, transparent 25%),
                linear-gradient(-45deg, #ccc 25%, transparent 25%),
                linear-gradient(45deg, transparent 75%, #ccc 75%),
                linear-gradient(-45deg, transparent 75%, #ccc 75%);
            background-size: 20px 20px;
            background-position: 0 0, 0 10px, 10px -10px, -10px 0px;
            padding: 2em;
            margin: 1em 0;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Transparent Background Testing</h1>

    <div class="transparency-demo">
        <h2>Semi-Transparent Red Background</h2>
        <p>This section has a semi-transparent red background (rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.3)).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="overlay-demo">
        <h2>Blue Overlay</h2>
        <p>This section has a semi-transparent blue background with white text.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="checkerboard">
        <h2>Transparency Pattern</h2>
        <p>This checkerboard pattern helps visualize transparency in the generated image.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Testing Notes</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Test image capture with transparent backgrounds</li>
        <li>Verify alpha channel preservation</li>
        <li>Check semi-transparent element rendering</li>
    </ul>
</body>
</html>